      "name": "Business Email Compromise Attacks Surge 45% Targeting Finance and Legal Sectors",
      "description": "Proofpoint's quarterly threat report documents a 45% year-on-year increase in business email compromise (BEC) attacks across its customer base. Finance, insurance, and legal sectors account for over 60% of observed incidents. Attackers are exploiting compromised Microsoft 365 accounts as launch platforms, using the trusted sender reputation to bypass email filtering. A growing proportion of attacks feature AI-generated email content that closely mimics executive writing styles, significantly increasing their effectiveness. Average financial loss per successful BEC incident reached $287,000 in Q1 2025. Organisations are urged to implement DMARC, enforce MFA on all email accounts, and provide regular security awareness training.",
